---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About">
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6 py-16">
    <div class="mb-12">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">About</p>
      <h1 class="text-4xl leading-tight">James Londrigan</h1>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-12 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_260px]">
      <!-- Main content -->
      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          I grew up watching my dad work in operational technology — the unglamorous,
          mission-critical layer that keeps physical systems running — and that's where the
          interest started. I came to Texas A&M thinking I'd do networking. I took ISTM 310, was
          sure that was the path, and then the more I learned about cloud, the more it pulled me
          up the stack.
        </p>
        <p>
          These days I'm a year into the MS-MIS program at Mays (graduating December 2026),
          working as a Business Development Program Aide at AgriLife CMTS, and chasing what cloud
          and AI can do for the businesses (and the people) on the receiving end of them. Three
          AWS certs in — Cloud Practitioner, AI Practitioner, and Solutions Architect Associate.
          Third place in the ISTM 320 CMIS Case Competition for an AI-driven IT strategy. Built
          the event service for the multi-team CMIS Engagement Platform on AWS serverless — that's
          its own <a href="/projects/cmis" class="text-maroon hover:underline underline-offset-2">case study</a>.
          Most recently rebuilt this site you're reading from Astro through Terraform to GitHub
          Actions, because if I'm going to talk about cloud, the cloud I built should be visible.
        </p>
        <p>
          The most interesting work in IT right now sits between cloud architecture and AI —
          specifically the part where these tools have to fit the messy reality of how a business
          actually operates, not the demo-day version. That overlap is where I want to spend the
          next few years.
        </p>
        <p>
          Outside of school and work: deep in the <em>Red Rising</em> saga (currently on
          <em>Iron Gold</em>), studying for my next cert, and probably overthinking my Terraform
          module structure.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Sidebar -->
      <aside class="space-y-10">
        <!-- Photo placeholder -->
        <div
          class="w-full aspect-square bg-paper border border-ink/10 flex items-center justify-center"
        >
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-muted text-center leading-loose">
            [Photo<br />coming soon]
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Currently -->
        <div>
          <p class="text-xs font-mono text-muted uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Currently</p>
          <dl class="space-y-3 text-sm">
            <div>
              <dt class="text-muted">Building</dt>
              <dd>This site — Astro, Terraform, AWS</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt class="text-muted">Reading</dt>
              <dd><em>Iron Gold</em> (Red Rising)</dd>
            </div>
            <div>
              <dt class="text-muted">Learning</dt>
              <dd>Agentic AI</dd>
            </div>
          </dl>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>
